page.title: 14 Worlingham Fete
page.content: At Worlingham Fete there are lots of side stalls . Such as coconut stall , drink stall, sweet stall,toy stall,and more.Some people entertain doing singing.Worlingham Middle School does a Gymnastics Display and Orchestra performance.The Fete is usually held in Lord Coville,s grounds.You can go and look round the Hall if you want to. If it rains it is held in the Village Hall.There is a play square for little children.Every year about 300 people attend.There aren't so many people attend if it is held indoors and there are only eight stalls.Most years they hold a tug of war competition.The Fete usually starts at 2 o'clock and ends at 5 o'clock .The money goes to the Church Funds.
